POGISHO Moagi (28) has
been handed a hefty sentence by the Mothibistad Regional Court. He stabbed and nearly
killed his mamazala with a pair of scissors after she denied him access to see
her daughter. Pogisho was found guilty
and convicted on a count of attempted murder. During court proceedings. Police spokesman Captain
Olebogeng Tawana said, “It emerged that the accused went to the 58-year-old
woman's house demanding to see her daughter who was the accused's girlfriend at
that time. The incident happened on 05 November 2021 at approximately 19h00 at
Manyeding village near Mothibistad.’ Tawana said the argument
between the accused and the 58-year-old victim ensued when she refused him to
see her daughter. He took out a pair of scissors and stab the victim multiple
times in the upper body. “As a result of the
attack, the victim is permanently paralysed. The accused was arrested shortly
after the incident and was released on R1000-00 bail. “On Wednesday, 20 July
2022 the accused was found guilty as charged and sentenced to twelve years
imprisonment on Thursday, 21 July 2022.” READ: BABES VS MAMAZALA: The gloves are off! Major General Otola
praised the investigating officer, Sergeant Thabo Phiri for his excellent
investigative work and for the synergy he displayed by working with the
National Prosecuting Authority(NPA) and Department of Justice (DoJ). "The
sentence will serve as a deterrent to perpetrators committing gender-based
violence.